		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037325.html">Quests and Inventory Slots</a></B><P>

<I>Something to keep in mind. Some quests will give you an item that requires a whole inventory slot (one of your main slots). If you do not have an open slot the item will fall to the ground. We all know that items that fall to the ground are not secure, and are not subject to reimbursement. So PLEASE make certain that you have an open inventory slot (at least one) when attempting quests.<P>

Alan</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037305.html">BUG: GUI and Alt-M problems</a></B><P>

This is a bug that deals with the new UI window that contains the Socials and Abilities button, etc.
Hitting Alt-M hides the Socials window but the window still intercepts all mouse clicks.<P>

<B>We've got that one fixed. It should be fixed with the patch on Thursday.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037301.html">I just got velious BUT......</a></B><P>

Where are my spell information. In fact all you you have in the box that is usefull is the cd, cdkey, and a city map. The lack of information is rediculous. Its like saying "install the game and you figure it out". I want to know some basic information suchs at what spells are available. Or if they are "found upon the minions of Vesshan" or something jeez.<P>

<B>All sorts of nifty stuff can be discovered if you read the fiction…<P>

But keep in mind, Velious is for people with characters of about 30th level and over. By now you should be aware that we don’t spell everything out for you. We give you enough information to discover the answers on your own. We encourage you to explore Velious and learn about the place, it's inhabitants and their treasure (which might become your treasure) on your own.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037299.html">hrm</a></b><P>

Hrm, yes , I agree with you Alan, but the power you hold to say, your not going to allow a thread to continue based on someone's opinion. Let it be creud or now.. is sorta called 'censorship' IMO<P>

<B>Actually, there are rules against such things. We don’t allow people to flame each other. Calling someone a nazi is a flame, it's a personal attack that I won't allow, directed at me, Verant, our customers or anyone else for that matter. I have no problem with people discussing issues and disagreeing with our policies. But I won't allow people to attack each other that way.<P>

You may call it censorship if you like. But it is against the rules set up for this board.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037105.html">**Mage Epic Weapon Completed on E'CI**</a></B><P>

Stats are: <P>

Orb of Mastery <BR>
MAGIC LORE ITEM NO DROP <BR>
Charge 1 <BR>
1HB 20 30 <BR>
Effect Manifest Elements <BR>
STR +15, STA +10, DEX +5, INT +20, MANA +100, save fire/cold +20, save magic +10 <P>

It is a summoned object from the spell: Summon Orb (level 46, 500 mana). <P>

Effect is an elemental, very huge with the air elemental graphic.<P>

<B>Just FYI: the pet doesn't do Dispel.<P>

I'm glad you all like this item, I sure do.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037048.html">Two bugs with this latest patch, proven and reproducable! Read to avoid</a></B><P>

The new ALT M menu is neat, but even when you turn it off it's "there". I put it in the middle of my screen then figured out it was ALT+M to turn it off. I turn it off, yet I find I cant left/right click in the middle of the window for targetting or mouselooking. When I move the box out of the way I can at least look around, but wherever it is on the screen real estate, it causes a problem.<P>

Second bug is with money splitting in the group. I was using /split 20 0 0 0 to split money with my partner (A good way to force PP on a cleric friend . Anyways I only had 20 on me at the time, so I split that, then got 10pp back. I typed /split 10 0 0 0 to split the remainder. When I did this, it said to wait a bit (I think thats what it said, terrible grammar on that error message) yet my plat went *poof*. Not a big deal since a small amount, just keep it in mind.<P>

<B>We're aware of the problem with that window. Right now the suggestion is to drag that window out of the way as much as possible before closing it. That's for now. We're fixing it so that the box will go away properly as soon as we can.<P>

We're also aware of the second bug too. You won't lose them money, it's still in a buffer someplace. It will come back when you zone or log back in. We're fixing that one too.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/037035.html">um, i have a website to report</a></b><P>

I don't want to put the link here or why it should be up, who should i email the information too, it has alot to do with exploiting, and many other things.<P>

<B>Send the link to me at <a href="mailto:avancouvering@verant.com">avancouvering@verant.com</a><P>

Thanks.<P>

Alan</B>
